The Crop Trust operates as an essential element of the funding strategy of the International Treaty on Plant Genetic Resources for Food and Agriculture (Treaty), as established in a formal Relationship Agreement signed by the Crop Trust and the Governing Body of the Treaty in 2006. There are 132 contracting parties to the Treaty (131 countries and the European Union) as of 2014.&#xd;
